        "comment": "Over a wide area 15 to 40 cm of snow has fallen since Sunday above approximately 1600 m. Over a wide area 10 to 15 cm of snow, and even more in some localities, will fall on Thursday above approximately 1600 m. The wind will be strong. <br/> Adjacent to ridgelines and in pass areas snow depths vary greatly, depending on the infuence of the wind. The snowpack is unfavourably layered. <br/> Faceted weak layers exist in the old snowpack in particular on west, north and east facing slopes. <br/> Isolated medium-sized to large natural dry avalanches have been released on Tuesday."
